subtitleNullable: 32x32 Pixel Digital Elevation Models, Categorized by Land Cover Type
descriptionNullable:
A collection of Land Cover-classified images from North Carolina. LiDAR data was taken from the State Census; the Land Cover classification was taken from the National Land Cover Database. 

Each image is a 32x32 pixel grayscale .tif image. The darkness of the pixel represents the height above sea level, and each pixel represents 20 feet of land. Every image in this dataset contains only the land cover of it's corresponding filename (i.e. Forest000001 is a 32x32 image of a forest, with no other land covers present in the image).
